# Start the app in subproject a under runReload (root does NOT have a main).
> a/runReload
> a/waitForStart

# runReload must have written a's capture file with the marker.
> a/assertCaptured

# From the aggregate root, the running Compile runReload fork must be visible
# (this is what lets bare `reloadOutput` at the root surface a subproject's output).
> assertRunningForkVisible

# The user's scenario: bare `reloadOutput` at the aggregate root. With the fix it
# reads the running fork's capture file (subproject a) and prints OUTPUT_MARKER_A,
# instead of "no output captured yet". Runs once because reloadOutput/aggregate=false.
> reloadOutput
